The paper deals with theoretical models for wireless sensor networks, which are typically studied in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The focus on complexity classes and computability also suggests the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) and Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Finally, the use of symmetric predicates and simulations of Turing Machines suggests the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
